<subSubSection id="CAD9656FFFCF8028FF40FD9AFF12FD86" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="827C36E4FFCF8028FF40FD9AFF12FD86" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis id="B0B7EAF6FFCF8028FF40FD9AFEACFDA2" bold="true" box="[199,337,514,539]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name of 
<taxonomicName id="45C34D67FFCF8028FDD2FD9BFD1EFDA2" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" box="[597,739,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis id="B0B7EAF6FFCF8028FDD2FD9BFD1EFDA2" box="[597,739,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">C. angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the acute angle formed by the paracephalon of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CAD9656FFFCF8028FF40FDD2FB93FD3E" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="827C36E4FFCF8028FF40FDD2FB93FD3E" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,647]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis id="B0B7EAF6FFCF8028FF40FDD2FEACFDDA" bold="true" box="[199,337,586,611]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="45C34D67FFCF8028FEDAFDD3FE12FDDA" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" box="[349,495,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis id="B0B7EAF6FFCF8028FEDAFDD3FE12FDDA" box="[349,495,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">C. angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive for its completely yellow body and swollen conical paracephalon (pointing dorsally) in combination with a smooth epicephalon and striate spermathecae.
</paragraph>
